        <content><![CDATA[<p>In the tab "Element settings" you can configure <a href="%(link0)">Element settings</a>. These settings are shown when you click the <img style="width: 14px;" title="propertyBigIconActive" src="%(link1)" alt="" /> symbol at an element that is rendered with the formatter. The content editor can alter these settings to adjust the behavior of the formatter.&nbsp;You can also link to a configuration file with already configured <a href="%(link2)">common element settings</a>, which are reused by many other formatters.</p>
<p>In the tab "<a href="%(link3)">Meta mappings</a>", you can set which values should be available to the page template as a meta mapping.</p>]]></content>
